ABS(3)                                                                         Linux Programmer's Manual                                                                        ABS(3)

NNAAMMEE
       abs, labs, llabs, imaxabs - compute the absolute value of an integer

SSYYNNOOPPSSIISS
       ##iinncclluuddee <<ssttddlliibb..hh>>

       iinntt aabbss((iinntt _j));;
       lloonngg llaabbss((lloonngg _j));;
       lloonngg lloonngg llllaabbss((lloonngg lloonngg _j));;

       ##iinncclluuddee <<iinnttttyyppeess..hh>>

       iinnttmmaaxx__tt iimmaaxxaabbss((iinnttmmaaxx__tt _j));;

   Feature Test Macro Requirements for glibc (see ffeeaattuurree__tteesstt__mmaaccrrooss(7)):

       llllaabbss():
           _ISOC99_SOURCE || _POSIX_C_SOURCE >= 200112L

DDEESSCCRRIIPPTTIIOONN
       The aabbss() function computes the absolute value of the integer argument _j.  The llaabbss(), llllaabbss(), and iimmaaxxaabbss() functions compute the absolute value of the argument _j of the ap‐
       propriate integer type for the function.

RREETTUURRNN VVAALLUUEE
       Returns the absolute value of the integer argument, of the appropriate integer type for the function.

AATTTTRRIIBBUUTTEESS
       For an explanation of the terms used in this section, see aattttrriibbuutteess(7).

       ┌──────────────────────────────────┬───────────────┬─────────┐
       │IInntteerrffaaccee                         │ AAttttrriibbuuttee     │ VVaalluuee   │
       ├──────────────────────────────────┼───────────────┼─────────┤
       │aabbss(), llaabbss(), llllaabbss(), iimmaaxxaabbss() │ Thread safety │ MT-Safe │
       └──────────────────────────────────┴───────────────┴─────────┘
CCOONNFFOORRMMIINNGG TTOO
       POSIX.1-2001, POSIX.1-2008, C99, SVr4, 4.3BSD.  C89 only includes the aabbss() and llaabbss() functions; the functions llllaabbss() and iimmaaxxaabbss() were added in C99.

NNOOTTEESS
       Trying to take the absolute value of the most negative integer is not defined.

       The llllaabbss() function is included in glibc since version 2.0.  The iimmaaxxaabbss() function is included in glibc since version 2.1.1.

       For llllaabbss() to be declared, it may be necessary to define __IISSOOCC9999__SSOOUURRCCEE or __IISSOOCC99XX__SSOOUURRCCEE (depending on the version of glibc) before including any standard headers.

       By default, GCC handles aabbss(), llaabbss(), and (since GCC 3.0) llllaabbss() and iimmaaxxaabbss() as built-in functions.

SSEEEE AALLSSOO
       ccaabbss(3), cceeiill(3), ffaabbss(3), fflloooorr(3), rriinntt(3)

